  ('Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat', 'rear-foot-elevated-split-squat-kicking', 'Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat uses hip flexion, knee flexion, hip extension to improve a key kicking-athlete problem: Builds high-value support-leg strength for planting, pivoting, decelerating, and re-accelerating around kicks and soccer strikes.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 4, 45, 90, 135, 'Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat is a Capacity exercise for kicking athletes that trains unilateral squat strength with direct carryover to support-leg force, plant-leg strength, kick recovery.', 'Primary subrole: squat_knee_dominant_strength. Coach this as Capacity work: preserve the intended phase, dose the drill by quality, and connect every rep to support-leg control, hip action, trunk transfer, and safe reset behavior.', 'Front leg does the work; pelvis stays level.', 'Unilateral squat strength', 'capacity', 'squat_knee_dominant_strength', 'rear_foot_elevated_split_squat_kicking_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip flexion","knee flexion","hip extension","single-leg stance"],"primary_tissues":["quadriceps","glutes","adductors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"medium","balance_demand":"medium","coordination_demand":"medium","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Perform Rear-Foot-Elevated Split Squat with attention to hip flexion, knee flexion, hip extension, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with bench, dumbbells and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to support-leg force, plant-leg strengt