  ('Cossack Squat', 'cossack-squat-kicking', 'Cossack Squat uses hip abduction, knee flexion, ankle dorsiflexion to improve a key kicking-athlete problem: Develops strength through lateral hip and adductor ranges that kickers need but often only stretch passively.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 4, 45, 90, 135, 'Cossack Squat is a Capacity exercise for kicking athletes that trains frontal-plane strength and range with direct carryover to side kick strength, low kick defense, soccer lateral reach.', 'Primary subrole: frontal_plane_lower_body_strength. Coach this as Capacity work: preserve the intended phase, dose the drill by quality, and connect every rep to support-leg control, hip action, trunk transfer, and safe reset behavior.', 'Push the floor and own the side-to-side range.', 'Frontal-plane strength and range', 'capacity', 'squat_knee_dominant_strength', 'cossack_squat_kicking_adductor_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip abduction","knee flexion","ankle dorsiflexion"],"primary_tissues":["adductors","glutes","quadriceps"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"medium","balance_demand":"medium","coordination_demand":"medium","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Perform Cossack Squat with attention to hip abduction, knee flexion, ankle dorsiflexion, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with none, kettlebell and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to side kick strength, low kick defense so the athlete understands the transfer target without rushing the movement."],"exec