  ('Pallof Press with March', 'pallof-press-with-march', 'Pallof Press with March uses anti-rotation press, hip flexion march, pelvic control to improve a key kicking-athlete problem: Builds trunk stiffness against rotation while the legs move, a direct need for support-leg control during kicking and ball striking.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 4, 45, 90, 135, 'Pallof Press with March is a Capacity exercise for kicking athletes that trains anti-rotation stance control with direct carryover to anti-rotation support, kick recoil, soccer plant stability.', 'Primary subrole: trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control. Coach this as Capacity work: preserve the intended phase, dose the drill by quality, and connect every rep to support-leg control, hip action, trunk transfer, and safe reset behavior.', 'Press and march without letting the band turn you.', 'Anti-rotation stance control', 'capacity', 'trunk_pelvis_anti_movement_control', 'pallof_press_march_kicking_core_capacity', '{"primary_joint_actions":["anti-rotation press","hip flexion march","pelvic control"],"primary_tissues":["obliques","abdominals","hip flexors"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"medium","balance_demand":"medium","coordination_demand":"medium","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Perform Pallof Press with March with attention to anti-rotation press, hip flexion march, pelvic control, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with bands, cable and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to anti-rotation support, kick rec