  ('Heavy Sled Push', 'heavy-sled-push', 'Heavy Sled Push uses hip extension, knee extension, ankle drive to improve a key kicking-athlete problem: Builds concentric projection strength for entries, approaches, and short accelerations without the eccentric soreness of heavy sprint volume.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 3, 4, 45, 90, 135, 'Heavy Sled Push is a Capacity exercise for kicking athletes that trains locomotive force capacity with direct carryover to soccer approach speed, MMA entries, kickboxing pressure steps.', 'Primary subrole: locomotive_force_capacity. Coach this as Capacity work: preserve the intended phase, dose the drill by quality, and connect every rep to support-leg control, hip action, trunk transfer, and safe reset behavior.', 'Push the ground away and keep the ribs stacked.', 'Locomotive force capacity', 'capacity', 'squat_knee_dominant_strength', 'heavy_sled_push_kicking_projection_strength', '{"primary_joint_actions":["hip extension","knee extension","ankle drive","trunk brace"],"primary_tissues":["glutes","quadriceps","calves"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"medium","balance_demand":"low","coordination_demand":"low","impact_level":0}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Perform Heavy Sled Push with attention to hip extension, knee extension, ankle drive, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with sled and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to soccer approach speed, MMA entries so the athlete understands the transfer target without rushing the movement."],"executio