  ('Lateral Lunge Decel Stick', 'lateral-lunge-decel-stick', 'Lateral Lunge Decel Stick uses lateral deceleration, hip abduction, knee flexion to improve a key kicking-athlete problem: Builds the braking qualities needed when a kick misses, lands awkwardly, or must transition immediately into defense or a cut.', 'BEGINNER', 8, 2, 4, 40, 45, 85, 'Lateral Lunge Decel Stick is a Resilience exercise for kicking athletes that trains frontal-plane braking control with direct carryover to missed kick recovery, soccer lateral decel, MMA stance recovery.', 'Primary subrole: landing_braking_control. Coach this as Resilience work: preserve the intended phase, dose the drill by quality, and connect every rep to support-leg control, hip action, trunk transfer, and safe reset behavior.', 'Brake on the outside leg and hold the shape.', 'Frontal-plane braking control', 'resilience', 'landing_braking_control', 'lateral_lunge_decel_stick_kicking_resilience', '{"primary_joint_actions":["lateral deceleration","hip abduction","knee flexion","ankle control"],"primary_tissues":["adductors","glutes","quadriceps","calves"],"primary_motor_control_demands":[],"postural_shape":null,"breathing_demand":"low","balance_demand":"high","coordination_demand":"medium","impact_level":2}'::jsonb, '{"movement_description":"Perform Lateral Lunge Decel Stick with attention to lateral deceleration, hip abduction, knee flexion, then reset into a stance or position that would allow another kick, strike, or ball action.","setup":["Set up with none, dumbbells and enough open space for the athlete to move, pivot, and stop without crowding.","Explain the intended phase and quality gate before the first rep so the athlete knows whether this is access, skill, output, strength, resilience, conditioning, or restore work.","Establish stance foot pressure, rib-pelvis position, and a safe return/reset position before adding speed, load, target, or partner input.","Connect the drill to missed kick recovery, soccer latera